# Feature-Sliced Design

## Module Structure

Every feature lives in `src/features/{name}/` with this structure:

```
features/{name}/
├── api/          # TanStack Query hooks (useXxx.ts)
├── components/   # UI components (XxxCard.tsx, XxxList.tsx)
├── hooks/        # Feature-specific hooks
├── screens/      # Screen components (XxxScreen.tsx)
├── store/        # Zustand slices (optional)
├── types.ts      # Feature-specific types
└── validation/   # Zod schemas (optional)
```

## Import Rules

```
✅ feature → shared          (always allowed)
✅ feature → packages/*      (always allowed)
❌ feature → another feature (NEVER — extract to shared/)
✅ app/    → features/*      (navigation wiring only)
✅ app/    → shared           (providers, theme)
```

If two features need the same logic, move it to `src/shared/`.

## File Naming

- Components: `PascalCase.tsx` (e.g., `MealCard.tsx`)
- Hooks: `camelCase.ts` prefixed with `use` (e.g., `useScanAnalysis.ts`)
- Utils/constants: `camelCase.ts` (e.g., `imageProcessing.ts`)
- Types: `types.ts` per feature, or `camelCase.ts` in `shared/types/`
- Screens: `PascalCase.tsx` suffixed with `Screen` (e.g., `DashboardScreen.tsx`)

## Feature Registry

Active features: `auth`, `onboarding`, `scanner`, `meals`, `diet-plan`, `chat`, `progress`, `dashboard`, `notifications`. New features must follow the same structure.

## Shared Code (`src/shared/`)

```
shared/
├── api/          # Supabase client, error handler, response types
├── components/   # SkeletonLoader, ErrorBoundary, EmptyState, AnimatedTransition
├── constants/    # nutrition.ts (RDA values), config.ts
├── hooks/        # useAppState, useNetworkStatus, useHealthData
├── theme/        # tokens.ts, lightTheme.ts, darkTheme.ts
├── types/        # nutrition.ts, user.ts, common.ts
└── utils/        # dateTime.ts, unitConversion.ts, validation.ts
```
